## 4. What Was Implemented vs. Future Work

### ✅ Implemented
- Brute-force similarity search (baseline)
- Chunked search (memory-efficient brute-force, one file at a time)
- **IVF (Inverted File Index)** search — fully integrated into the model
- SemDeDup for trace data deduplication
- Expert prediction with snapshot optimization (one IVF search per token)
- Expert preloading with mmap, dual-queue, stale expert release
- Memory optimizations: MALLOC_ARENA_MAX=2, memmap trace storage, no double storage of weights
- C++ and Python implementations of both IVF and HNSW

### 🔮 Future Work
- **HNSW integration** into the model (currently only benchmarked standalone, not integrated into `expert_tracer.py`)
- Fix prefetching pipeline (snapshot mechanism not fully triggering `enqueue_prefetch` during inference)
- Pre-build all needed IVF indexes offline (currently some built lazily)
- GPU acceleration (currently running on CPU)
- Quantization of expert weights for further memory savings

